            "is_major": false,
            "source": "Benzinga",
            "source_type": "news",
            "summary": "Crombie Real Estate Investment Trust reported strong performance for the fourth quarter and year ended December 31, 2024. Operational highlights include a committed occupancy of 96.8% and economic occupancy of 96.5%, with a 30 basis point and 50 basis point increase, respectively, from the previous year. Strategic acquisitions and dispositions were made, including the acquisition of Zephyr residential for $133,000 and the sale of two retail assets for $6,000. Financially, the trust completed offerings of $300,000 Series M senior unsecured notes and redeemed $175,000 principal amount of Series E senior unsecured notes. In the fourth quarter of 2024, property revenue was $121,595, FFO per unit was $0.32, and AFFO per unit was $0.28, showing increases in various financial metrics. The full story can be found on Benzinga.com.",
